## 1. Authoritative Plan/Entitlement State

### Finding: Two sources, one winner

| Field | Table | Written by | Read by iOS | Read by Android |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `subscription_tier` | `clubs` | stripe-webhook, cancel-club-subscription, expire-subscriptions, admin_force_expire_subscription | **Never** | **Never** (doc-only) |
| `plan_tier` | `club_entitlements` | `derive_club_entitlements()` only | Yes ‚Äî FeatureGateService, ClubDashboardView, plan badge | Yes (planned) |
| `plan_type` | `club_subscriptions` | stripe-webhook, create-club-subscription, cancel-club-subscription | No (internal) | No |

**Rule confirmed:** `club_entitlements.plan_tier` is the single authoritative source for feature gating in all clients.
`clubs.subscription_tier` is a denormalised write-through field maintained by backend services only. iOS never reads it. Android planning docs say read-only, but `android_build/system_contracts.me:155` incorrectly calls it "the authoritative field" ‚Äî this is a documentation error (see Section 8).

